			<SecondaryPreamble>
				<IntroductoryText>
					<P>
						<Text>Whereas the Public Lending Right Scheme 1982<FootnoteRef Ref="f00001"/> (“the Scheme”) was brought into force on 14th June 1982;</Text>
					</P>
					<P>
						<Text Hanging="indented">Whereas the Scheme has been varied<FootnoteRef Ref="f00002"/>;</Text>
					</P>
					<P>
						<Text Hanging="indented">And whereas the Secretary of State, after consultation with the representatives of authors and library authorities and of others who appear likely to be affected, has further varied the Scheme;</Text>
					</P>
				</IntroductoryText>
				<EnactingText>
					<Para>
						<Text Hanging="indented">Now, therefore, the Secretary of State, in exercise of the powers conferred by section 3(7) of the Public Lending Right Act 1979<FootnoteRef Ref="f00003"/> and now vested in him<FootnoteRef Ref="f00004"/>, hereby makes the following Order:–</Text>
					</Para>
				</EnactingText>
			</SecondaryPreamble>
		</SecondaryPrelims>
		<Body>
			<P1>
				<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
				<P1para>
					<Text>This Order may be cited as the Public Lending Right Scheme 1982 (Commencement of Variations) Order 2000.</Text>
				</P1para>
			</P1>
			<P1>
				<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
				<P1para>
					<Text>The variation in the Public Lending Right Scheme 1982 which was made on 30th March 2000 by the Secretary of State and is set out in the Appendix to this Order shall come into force on 1st July 2000.</Text>
				</P1para>
			</P1>

